    <text type="letter">
        <body>
           <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.00224_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden Sunday P M<ptr target="loc.04004_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1887-07-24">July 24 '87</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Well, Hank dear boy, how are you standing it this hot summer? Eva<ptr target="n6107"/> I want you to write
                to me &amp; tell me. We have had it fearful hot &amp; tainted here for over seven
                weeks, but I am alive &amp; kicking yet&#8212;it is rainy to-day but warm
                yet&#8212;I shall drive down to your parents<ptr target="loc.02189_n3"/> in a day or two&#8212;(intended to have
                gone to-day)&#8212;Nothing very new with me, much the same old story&#8212;H
                    G<ptr target="n0262"/> is here yet&#8212;the sculptor Morse<ptr
                    target="n0862"/> also&#8212;I remain in good spirits but a pretty bad case
                bodily.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Love to you &amp; E &amp; the little one<ptr target="n6119"/></salute>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_vm.00223_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
